<item>
            <title>[TIKA-472] Extract image title, description and author</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-472</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the JPEG+TIFF metadata extractor reads embedded keywords but not comments. There are XMP/IPTC fields that map nicely to the metadata fields AUTHOR, TITLE and DESCRIPTION. This is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-314&quot; title=&quot;Initial support for JPEG EXIF metadata extraction&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and the XMP discussion in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-442&quot; title=&quot;Image extractors use inconsistent metadata keys and formats for common features&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-442&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-442&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch adds parsing of these fields as set in XMP applications such as Photoshop: Object Name (Title), Caption (Description) and By-Line (Author).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
